1. Create class Person
2. which has the following attributes:
 name, sex, religion,
 language spoken, job,
 nationality, EGN,
 date of birth, age,
 country of residence.
3. The date of birth attribute and age
 are composed during the creation of an
 object based on the EGN.
4. EGN consists of 10 digits.
5. If provided value for EGN or
 sex are not correct throw exception.
6. If wrong sex is provided program
 must continue its normal execution
 with printing relevant message.
7. Only job and country of residence
 could change their values.
8. All other attributes can`t be
 changes once they are set.
